                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaffer",
                        "name": "kaffer",
                        "displayName": "Curtis Kaffer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "By requiring 'content' you seem to be insisting that custom adapters will use it. This is not always the case. I have an adapter that does real-time translation via a web service. It isn't relying on local files.\r\n\r\nI believe it should be up to the individual adapter to decide if a certain option is required.",
